AMERICAN AIRLINES SECURES WIRELESS LANS IN DENVER
(Source: Computerworld) American Airlines has made sweeping
changes to improve wireless security. But public airport WLANs
are still a haven for hacker activity.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779594

OS 6 TO FEATURE BETTER WIRELESS INTEGRATION, PALM SAYS
(Source: ITworld.com) Palm's fifth-generation operating system
have only just started emerging but the company is already
dropping hints about what users can expect in Palm OS 6.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779595

MICROSOFT LAUNCHES U.S. SMARTPHONE PUSH
(Source: Computerworld) Microsoft and two hardware makers are
announcing mobile phones that run Microsoft's Smartphone software
and can be used on cellular networks in the U.S.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779596

YAO MING TO STAR IN WIRELESS GAME FOR CHINA
(Source: IDG.net) Wireless game developer Sorrent has announced
plans to release a game for mobile phones based on Chinese
basketball player Yao Ming.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779597

MICROSOFT RELEASES SECOND BETA OF EXCHANGE 2003
(Source: IDG.net) Microsoft released another test version of an
upgrade of its Exchange messaging and information management
server software, as it prepares to enhance access to e-mail by
mobile users.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779598


